{
  "text": "The coccygeal vertebral disc degeneration and leakage of NP were done by needle puncture according to Bin Han process [CITATION_1] with some modifications. The needle penetrated into the center of the disc until it reached the opposite side of the tail, and then, needle was rotated 360\u00b0a nd held for 30 s before extraction. This protocol been reported to affect both disc height index and histological score of disc degeneration significantly [CITATION_2] . The segments of tail puncture were on the disc between the Co7/Co8 and Co8/Co9. The size of needle is 18-g, which has been reported to make the best effect on induction of the disc degeneration [CITATION_3] . In order to avoid infection, each needle was discarded after single use. The procedure was performed under radiography to ensure that the needle was inserted into the correct place.",
  "correct_citation": {
